content.text:
Root cause: `SingleFragmentActivity.dispatchKeyEvent()` always delegates **all** key events to the hosted fragment when it implements `DispatchKeyEventListener`. If the fragment returns `false` (not handled), the activity **still does not call `super.dispatchKeyEvent()`**, so the system BACK key never reaches the default back handling. `PreviewerFragment` implements `DispatchKeyEventListener` but doesn’t handle `KEYCODE_BACK`, so the Android back button does nothing.

Fix: only consume the event when the fragment reports it handled it; otherwise fall back to the normal activity dispatch.

Changed file:
- `AnkiDroid/src/main/java/com/ichi2/anki/SingleFragmentActivity.kt`

```kotlin
override fun dispatchKeyEvent(event: KeyEvent): Boolean {
    val fragment = supportFragmentManager.findFragmentById(R.id.fragment_container)!!
    if (fragment is DispatchKeyEventListener && fragment.dispatchKeyEvent(event)) {
        return true
    }
    return super.dispatchKeyEvent(event)
}
```

This restores Android back button behavior in the previewer while keeping the previewer’s DPAD/keyboard shortcuts working.

